summary: SANTA CLARA, Calif., Feb. 03, 2026 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- AMD (NASDAQ:AMD) today announced financial results for the fourth quarter and full year of 2025. headline: Disney, PayPal name new CEOS: Why this matters
summary: HP Inc. (HPQ) CEO Enrique Lores announced that he will be leaving the company to be the chief executive at PayPal (PYPL), while Disney (DIS) has officially named its parks division chairman Josh D'Amaro to be its next CEO after Bob Iger. Yahoo Finance Executive Editor Brian Sozzi reports on these latest C-suite shakeups. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out Yahoo Finance.

headline: G2 Names Alexis Zheng Chief Product and Technology Officer to Drive AI Innovation and Platform Growth
summary: G2, the world's largest and most trusted software marketplace, today announced the appointment of Alexis Zheng as Chief Product and Technology Officer. In her role, Zheng will help accelerate strategic growth and scale innovation as the company advances its vision to be the most trusted data source for B2B software and go-to-market (GTM) decisions in the age of AI.

headline: Troubadour Tech Achieves HPE Juniper Networking Elite Plus Partner Status and Earns Medallion-to-Medallion Recognition
summary: Troubadour Tech, a leader in enterprise networking, cybersecurity infrastructure, and IT solutions, today announced it has achieved Elite Plus Partner status with HPE Networks. In addition, Troubadour has been invited to participate in HPE's Medallion-to-Medallion program, an exclusive recognition awarded to the top 1% of partners globally based on exceptional combined performance across Juniper Networks and HPE solutions.

headline: HPE to Present Live Audio Webcast of Fiscal 2026 First Quarter Earnings Conference Call
summary: HOUSTON, February 03, 2026--HPE (NYSE: HPE) will conduct a live audio webcast of a conference call with analysts to review financial results for the first quarter of fiscal 2026, ending January 31, 2026.
